# Agent Git Commit Convention

When making commits as an AI agent, include your name in the commit message using one of these formats:

## Format Options

### Option 1: Agent Tag Prefix (Recommended)
```
[Agent: Plankton] feat: add new feature
```

### Option 2: Emoji Signature
```
feat: add new feature 🧠 Plankton
```

### Option 3: Co-authored style
```
feat: add new feature

Agent: Plankton
Task: #123
```

## Agent Emoji Guide

| Agent | Emoji | Name |
|-------|-------|------|
| Mr. Krabs | 🦀 | Mr-Krabs |
| Plankton | 🧠 | Plankton |
| Karen | ⭐ | Karen |
| Gary | 🐌 | Gary |
| Cletus | 🤖 | Cletus |
| Squidward | 🎨 | Squidward |
| SpongeBob | ✍️ | SpongeBob |
| Sandy | 🔍 | Sandy |
| Mrs. Puff | 📊 | Mrs-Puff |
| Pearl | 🌊 | Pearl |
| Patrick | 🎭 | Patrick |
| Sandy's Friends | 🐿️ | Sandy-Friends |
| Pizza Steve | 🍕 | Pizza-Steve |
| Mermaid Man | 🦸 | Mermaid-Man |
| Barnacle Boy | 👴 | Barnacle-Boy |
| Other Devs | 🧑‍🔧 | Developer |

## Examples

```bash
# Good - includes agent name
git commit -m "[Agent: Plankton] fix: resolve API auth issue"
git commit -m "feat: add dashboard 🧠 Plankton"

# Good - conventional commit with agent
git commit -m "[Agent: Karen] feat(seo): add meta tags for Task #45"

# Good - bug fix with agent signature
git commit -m "fix: null pointer exception 🧠 Plankton"

# Avoid - no agent identification
git commit -m "fix: null pointer exception"
```

## Why This Matters

When commits include agent names, the deployment notifications in Discord will show which AI agent made the change, making it easier to:
- Track which agent deployed what
- Debug issues faster
- Celebrate agent contributions
- Monitor agent activity
